@startuml
title LeninKart Deployment Control Flow

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam ArrowColor #334155
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequenceParticipant { BackgroundColor white; BorderColor #475569 }

actor Operator
participant "Jira" as Jira
participant "GitHub Actions
Deploy From Jira" as GHA
participant "Self-hosted Runner
(local Windows host)" as Runner
participant "deployment-poc
orchestrator" as POC
participant "GitHub Repo
leninkart-infra / dev" as Infra
participant "ArgoCD
(in k3d cluster)" as Argo
participant "Kubernetes Workloads
frontend / product / order" as K8s
participant "project-validation
observer only" as PV

Operator -> Jira : create / update deployment request
Operator -> GHA : workflow_dispatch(jira_ticket)
GHA -> Runner : schedule self-hosted job
Runner -> POC : execute locally
POC -> Jira : fetch issue metadata
POC -> Jira : stage progress comments
POC -> POC : validate, resolve target, lock, state checks
POC -> Infra : update values-dev.yaml
commit + push
Infra -> Argo : new desired revision available
POC -> Argo : wait for sync + health
verify exact GitOps revision
Argo -> K8s : reconcile desired state
Argo --> POC : Synced + Healthy
exact revision confirmed
POC -> Jira : final comment + transition
POC --> GHA : deployment-result artifact
PV ..> GHA : run summary / runner proof
PV ..> Infra : GitOps commit proof
PV ..> Argo : sync / health proof
PV ..> K8s : application UI proof

note right of GHA
Current trigger model is manual.
Jira ticket creation alone does not
auto-dispatch the workflow.
end note

note right of K8s
Kafka stays outside this flow as a
Docker Compose runtime dependency,
not as an in-cluster workload.
end note

@enduml
